Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{0.5%tsp}. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Add the potatoes to the boiling water and cook until tender, ~{12-15%mins}.

> The potatoes are cooked when you can easily slip a knife through them.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium high heat. Put the @chicken breast{260%g}(diced) in a #bowl{} and add the @plain flour{8%g} and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Toss to coat. Once hot, add the chicken to the pan and stir-fry until golden brown, ~{4-5%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

While the chicken cooks, halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}. Trim the @green beans{80%g} and chop into thirds. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Once the chicken is browned, add the shallot, cook with the chicken until softened, ~{3-4%mins}. Stir in the garlic and @tomato puree{30%g}, cook for ~{1%minute}. Pour in the @water{150%ml} and add the @honey{15%g} and @chicken stock powder{1}. Stir in the green beans, bring to a simmer. Cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}, simmer until the beans are cooked and the sauce has thickened, ~{4-5%mins}.

Meanwhile, once the potatoes are cooked, drain them in a #colander{}. Pop them back in their pan and add a knob of @butter{30%g} and a splash of @?milk{30%ml}. Season to taste with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} and mash until smooth with a #potato masher{}.

Once the chicken and beans are cooked, season to taste with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Serve the mash on plates with the stew alongside and enjoy!

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.